  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to verfiy the hypothesis if a short intensive psychocardiological
      interval-intervention, combined with a structured follow up, decreases the rate of disability
      retirements caused by psychosocial co-morbidity of patients with coronary heart disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to verfiy the hypothesis if a short intensive psychocardiological
      interval intervention, combined with a structured follow up, decreases the rate of disability
      retirements caused by psychosocial co-morbidity of patients with coronary heart disease.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
